						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa (1490 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Incomplete. States that on behalf of Peruṅkoṇḍai Annadāta Da[ṇ*]ṇāyaka-Uḍaiyar of Harita-gōtra, certain offerings to god including a lamp and garlands were to be made from the income of lands in Uruttava [Be]mmana-aḷḷi <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śrīraṅgarājapuram in Mukkuṉṟa-nāḍu, a sub-division in Peruṅkoṇḍai-rājyam. The details of the date viz., <hi rend="bold">Sādhāraṇa, Puraṭṭāśi 12</hi> may be equated with <hi rend="bold">1490 A.D., September 11,</hi> since the record is palaeographically assignable to the <hi rend="bold">15th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
